  "@type": "Article",
  "description": "I think I’m finally at the point where the next thing to do is not invent anything new, but start organizing what already exists. I have years of files spread across repositories, moments, naming schemes, half-finished directions. None of it really means anything in isolation anymore. What I want is to be able to see it all at once, as parts of one semiotic universe, so that meaning emerges from adjacency rather than memory.\n",
  "name": "Organizing Toward a Semiotic Universe",
